and agencies that seek to test large-scale structural components, such as sections of roadways and bridges.   Find out more        CME Labs           Visit lab site             Visit lab site             Visit lab site             Visit lab site             Visit lab site             Visit lab site             Visit lab site           Additional CME Labs   The following labs in UIC civil and materials engineering have websites under development. Their sites will be added to the grid above as they launch.   Computational Mechanics Laboratory  Concrete Laboratory  Corrosion Laboratory  Environmental Biotechnology Laboratory  Environmental Separations Laboratory  Geomechanics Laboratory  High Temperature Laboratory  Nano Mechanics and Materials Laboratory  Structural Health Monitoring Laboratory  TransLab  Transportation Computational Laboratory   For more information on these labs, please email cme@uic.edu .          Research    Back to main content           High-Bay Structures Laboratory    Labs    Research Areas    Student Research Opportunities    Seminars                   UIC Logo         College of  Engineering           Quicklinks    Graduate Resources    Undergraduate Resources    Room Reservation Form    ABET Accreditation         Contact   Department of Civil and Materials Engineering  2095 Engineering Research Facility, 842 W. Taylor St., Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-3428  Fax: (312) 996-2426  cme@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 